1.speaker: PENGUIN
1.character: 笹子さん　肉じゃがが好きな男って　どう思う？
1.definition: Miss Sasako, how do you feel about menwho like meat and potato stew? I'd rather not answer right now, if that's okay.

4.speaker: PANDA
4.character: ねえ　僕　いまだに　自然体っていうのがわからないの
4.definition: You know, I still can't figure out this "act naturally" thing. Just act naturally.

5.speaker: PANDA
5.character: いくら考えても　答えが出なくて
5.definition: No matter how much I think about it, I can't find the answer.

6.speaker: PANDA
6.character: 常勤パンダさん　自然体って何？
6.definition: What does it mean to act naturally, Mr. Full-time Panda?

8.speaker: PANDA
8.definition: Hey, Mr. Handa, what does it mean to "act naturally"?

9.speaker: PANDA
9.character: 言ったでしょ　「自然体でいいです」って
9.definition: You said it yourself, "just act naturally."

10.speaker: HANDA
10.character: 自然でいることが　自然体じゃないかな
10.definition: I think the act of acting naturally is "acting natural." Could you give me an example?

13.speaker: PANDA
13.character: 自然体って　どういうことなの？
13.definition: What does it mean to "act naturally"?

15.speaker: PENGUIN
15.character: 自然体かどうか　わかんないけど　かわいいね
15.definition: I don't know if that's acting natural or not, but it is cute.

18.speaker: PENGUIN
18.character: もう　かわいいのは　わかったよ

20.speaker: PANDA
20.character: かわいい　かわいいって言われても　どうしていいか　わかんなくて
20.definition: I keep getting called cute, but I still don't know what to do.

21.speaker: LLAMA
21.character: いいなぁ　僕も　かわいいって　言われてみたいですよ
21.definition: How nice. I wish someone would call me cute.

22.speaker: PANDA
22.character: ゴロゴロしてるだけなのになぁ
22.definition: All I'm doing is lounging around. You always look like you're having fun. I'm jealous.

24.speaker: OTTER
24.character: 僕さ　お腹で貝割るでしょ？ヾ(≧へ≦)〃
24.definition: You know I break shellfish on my tummy, right?

25.speaker: OTTER
25.character: あれって大変だよ　お腹痛くなる
25.definition: It's harder than it looks. It hurts my tummy.

26.speaker: OTTER
26.character: お腹に石だよ　笹子さん
26.definition: I'm banging a rock on my tummy, Miss Sasako.

28.speaker: OTTER
28.character: 自分のお腹を石で叩いてみなよ
28.definition: You should try banging a rock on your tummy.

31.speaker: POLAR BEAR
31.character: お腹で割らなければいいのに
31.definition: Then you shouldn't try breaking it on your tummy. But the audience loves seeing that.

32.speaker: PENGUIN
32.character: もうやめたら？　その出し物
32.definition: Why don't you give up that act?

33.speaker: OTTER
33.character: 出し物っていうか　習性だからね
33.definition: It's not really an act. It's more of a trait.

34.speaker: LLAMA
34.character: かわいいから　いいじゃないですか
34.definition: I think it's fine since it's cute.

35.speaker: OTTER
35.character: かわいいんだけどさ　もう　お腹が限界
35.definition: It's cute, but my tummy's had enough.

36.speaker: KOALA
36.character: かわいいで言ったら　私も　かわいいんですけど
36.definition: Since we're on the topic of cute, I'm cute, too.

38.speaker: KOALA
38.character: ユーカリ？　かわいく食べてますけど　もう　あれ限界です
38.definition: I'm cutely eating eucalyptus, but I'm at my limit.

39.speaker: KOALA
39.definition: I'm sick of it. I eat about one kilogram of that stuff a day.

40.speaker: KOALA
40.definition: You'd get teary-eyed, too, if you had to do it.

41.speaker: ANTEATER
41.definition: I know! I totally get you!

43.speaker: ANTEATER
43.character: アリクイって　やめて！
43.definition: I don't like the name Anteater! I don't want to eat  only ants all the time! I'm sick of them!

44.speaker: ANTEATER
44.character: 笹子さん　アリばっかり食べる気持わかる？
44.definition: Do you know how it feels to have to eat ants all the time, Miss Sasako?! I'm sorry?! I can't say that I do.

46.speaker: POLAR BEAR
46.definition: You don't have much of a choice.

47.speaker: ANTEATER
47.character: 確かに　そうだけど　もっと　いろんなもの食べてみたいよ
47.definition: I know, but I want to eat other things, too!

50.speaker: ANTEATER
50.character: ほら　ラーメンとかさ

51.speaker: PANDA
51.character: チャーシュー食べられないんじゃない？
51.definition: But I don't think you can eat chashu pork.

52.speaker: ANTEATER
52.character: いいんだよ　細かいところは
52.definition: You don't have to be concerned with the little things.

53.speaker: LLAMA
53.character: 見てくれるだけ　いいじゃないですか
53.definition: At least people look at you.

55.speaker: LLAMA
55.character: 僕なんて　みんな　ほぼ素通りですよ
55.definition: Everyone pretty much passes right by me.

56.speaker: LLAMA
56.character: いるの　気づいてます？
56.definition: Did you even know I was there?

58.speaker: POLAR BEAR
58.definition: When we went to the zoo... We did pretty much pass right by.

59.speaker: LLAMA
59.character: ほらね　ラマなんて　そんなものですよ
59.definition: See? That's how it is, being a llama.

60.speaker: LLAMA
60.character: もっと　じっくり見たり
60.definition: I wish people would look longer,

61.speaker: LLAMA
61.character: 行列つくって　感想とか言ってほしいですΣ(　￣д￣　)
61.definition: and form huge lines to tell me what they think of me.

63.speaker: GUY
63.character: おい　見ろよ！　草食ってるぞ！　写真　写真撮れって！
63.definition: Look, it's eating grass! Hurry! Take a picture!

66.speaker: PENGUIN
66.character: ラマさんって　ロバなの？
66.definition: Are you a donkey, Mr. Llama?

67.speaker: LLAMA
67.definition: As I said, I'm a llama.

68.speaker: LLAMA
68.character: どっちかというと　ラクダです
68.definition: If you had to compare, I'm closer to a camel.

71.speaker: SASAKO
71.character: あの…　何か芸とかないんですか？
71.definition: Um... Can you do any tricks or anything?

72.speaker: LLAMA
72.character: 草を食べるくらいです

73.speaker: LLAMA
73.character: あと　まつ毛が長いです(￣y▽￣)╭
73.definition: Other than that, my eyelashes are very long.

74.speaker: POLAR BEAR
74.character: できるといいね　行列
74.definition: I hope you get that huge line of yours.

75.speaker: TAPIR
75.character: 見られればいいってもんじゃないよ
75.definition: Being looked at isn't all that great.

77.speaker: TAPIR
77.character: 僕なんて　夢を食べる動物って　言われがちだけど
77.definition: I'm rumored to be an animal that eats dreams,

78.speaker: TAPIR
78.character: 見た人に夢がないなんて　言われてさ
78.definition: but everyone who sees me is unimpressed.

79.speaker: TAPIR
79.character: 夢を食べる動物って何？
79.definition: What kind of animal eats dreams, anyway?

80.speaker: TAPIR
80.character: ハードル上げすぎなんだよ
80.definition: They're setting the bar much too high.

81.speaker: PENGUIN
81.character: まぁまぁ…　ジュゴンさんよりは　いいよ
81.definition: Now, now. You're better off than the sea cow.

82.speaker: PENGUIN
82.character: 人魚って　前振りされてるんだから

83.speaker: GIRL
83.character: ママ！　人魚さん　どこ？

84.speaker: PENGUIN
84.character: 見た人　みんな黙っちゃうよ
84.definition: Everyone who sees it doesn't know what to say.

86.speaker: SASAKO
86.character: 私に聞かないでください…

88.speaker: TAPIR
88.character: ジュゴンさんに比べたら　僕は　まだ　マシかもね
88.definition: If you compare me to Ms. Sea Cow, I'm probably better off.

91.speaker: SLOTH
91.character: 動物園とは関係ないけど…
91.definition: I'm not associated with the zoo, but...

92.speaker: SLOTH
92.character: 僕って　一日中　木に　ぶら下がってるイメージあるけど…
92.definition: People think I just hang from a tree all day.

94.speaker: SLOTH
94.character: 実際　そうだけど…　大変　腕　パンパン
94.definition: I do in reality... But it's hard. My arms tingle.

95.speaker: SLOTH
95.character: 一日中　木に　ぶら下がったことある？笹子さん
95.definition: Have you ever hung from a tree all day, Miss Sasako? I can't say that I have.

96.speaker: PENGUIN
96.character: ナマケモノくんって　ナマケモノじゃないな
96.definition: I guess Sloth isn't really a sloth.

99.speaker: PENGUIN
99.character: みんな悩んでるんだな

101.speaker: PENGUIN
101.character: 実は　好きなペンギンがいてさ
101.definition: You see, I have this penguin that I like.

102.speaker: PENGUIN
102.character: 誰にも　言わないでほしいんだけどね

103.speaker: LLAMA
103.character: あぁ　やっぱり　いろいろと　皆さん悩みが尽きないんですね
103.definition: It seems that there isn't an end to everyone's problems.

106.speaker: PENGUIN
106.character: ちょっと　聞いてよ

107.speaker: TAPIR
107.character: シロクマさんは　悩みはないの？
107.definition: Don't you have any problems, Mr. Polar Bear?

109.speaker: PENGUIN
109.character: え？　そうなの？　意外

110.speaker: POLAR BEAR
110.character: アイドルにならないかって　言われてるんだけど
110.definition: I've been asked if I wanted to become an idol,

111.speaker: POLAR BEAR
111.character: アイドルと学業の両立がねぇ
111.definition: but fitting that inwith my studies would be hard.

113.speaker: PENGUIN
113.definition: How about you, Miss Sasako? I don't have any.

115.speaker: SASAKO
115.definition: Indeed. What is it? I was wondering if Hina dolls should go with the burnable or non-burnable garbage.

116.speaker: PENGUIN
116.character: いいかな？　それは　あとで
116.definition: How about we discuss that later?

117.speaker: PENGUIN
117.character: 僕なんてさ　パン屋に行くたびに思うよ
117.definition: Every time I go to the bakery, I think about it.

118.speaker: PENGUIN
118.character: いい？　誰にも言わないでよ

119.speaker: PENGUIN
119.character: どうやって告白しようか　悩みは尽きないよ
119.definition: I keep trying to figure out how to ask her out.

120.speaker: PENGUIN
120.character: どう思う？　パンダくん

121.speaker: PENGUIN
121.character: ちょっと笑いごとじゃないよ
121.definition: Hey, this is no laughing matter.

123.speaker: LLAMA
123.definition: Hm... I wonder how long he's been asleep.

124.speaker: POLAR BEAR
124.character: チャーシューの話のあとくらいじゃない？
124.definition: Probably somewhere right after the talk of chashu pork. So somewhere at the beginning of the conversation. Oh, Mr. Polar Bear.

125.speaker: LLAMA
125.character: おかわり　お願いします

128.speaker: PANDA
128.character: どうしたら　いいんだろう…
128.definition: I wonder what I should do?

129.speaker: FT PANDA
129.character: パンダくん　すっかり自然体だね
129.definition: Panda is totally acting naturally right now.

134.speaker: PENGUIN
134.character: あれから　ずっと考えてたんだけどさ

135.speaker: PENGUIN
135.character: パンダくんにとって　自然体っていうのはさ

136.speaker: PENGUIN
136.character: 君が　いちばんリラックスできる場所
136.definition: being in the place you can relax the most.

139.speaker: PANDA
139.definition: Never mind that, Mr. Penguin. I bought new panda merchandise.

140.character: 何入れればいいと思う？O(*≧▽≦)ツ
140.definition: What do you think I should put in here?

141.speaker: PENGUIN
141.character: 肉まんでいいんじゃない？

142.speaker: PANDA
142.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

143.speaker: PANDA
143.character: しろくまカフェが来週から駐車場になっちゃうって本当
143.definition: Is it true that Polar Bear's Café is being turned into a parking lot next week?

144.speaker: PENGUIN
144.character: そんな噂　聞いてないよ
144.definition: I didn't hear a rumor like that. Are you sure you haven't had plastic surgery?

146.character: だから　逆にどこを見て思ったの
146.definition: I ask again, what makes you think I did?

147.speaker: PANDA
147.character: しろくまくん　終わって
147.definition: Polar Bear, could you finish it? Sure.

149.speaker: POLAR BEAR
149.definition: Hm... It's "Café." Did you actually forget?
